William Tessun of Ivelcester‚to Richard the son of Roger le Sepere and Alice his wife, a stall in Ivelcestre‚ close to the stall once belonging to Thomas Cabbel in Chepstrete‚ on the south3 and the house of Luke the Goldsmith on the north.

To Have . , . By a yearly payment of sixpeme, one half at Easter, the other half at Michaelmas. And to the Farm of

the said Town one penny on Hockeday. And to William Axstild one rose on the Feast of the Nativity of St. John the Baptist. For this grant, Richard and Alice pay four shillings sterling, down, to Willm Tessun.
